<lesson>
  <number>127</number>
  <title>A famous actress</title>
  <titleCn>著名的女演员</titleCn>
  <words>
    <word>
      <text>famous</text>
      <textCn>著名的</textCn>
    </word>
    <word>
      <text>actress</text>
      <textCn>女演员</textCn>
    </word>
    <word>
      <text>at least</text>
      <textCn>至少</textCn>
    </word>
    <word>
      <text>actor</text>
      <textCn>男演员</textCn>
    </word>
    <word>
      <text>read</text>
      <textCn>通过阅读得知</textCn>
    </word>
  </words>
  <sentences>
    <sentence>
      <text>Can you recognize that woman, Liz?</text>
      <textCn>莉兹，你能认出那个女人吗？</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I think I can, Kate.</text>
      <textCn>我想我认得出来，凯特。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>It must be Karen Marsh, the actress.</text>
      <textCn>那一定是女演员卡伦·马什。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I thought so.</text>
      <textCn>我也这样想。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Who's that beside her?</text>
      <textCn>她旁边的那个人是谁？</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>That must be Conrad Reeves.</text>
      <textCn>一定是康拉德·里弗斯。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Conrad Reeves, the actor?</text>
      <textCn>康拉德·里弗斯，那个男演员吗？</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>It can't be.</text>
      <textCn>不可能是。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Let me have another look.</text>
      <textCn>让我再看一看。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I think you're right!</text>
      <textCn>我想你是对的。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Isn't he her third husband?</text>
      <textCn>他不是她的第3个丈夫吗？</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>No.</text>
      <textCn>不。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>He must be her fourth or fifth.</text>
      <textCn>他一定是她的第4个或第5个丈夫。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Doesn't Karen Marsh look old!</text>
      <textCn>卡伦看上去不显老嘛！</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>She does, doesn't she!</text>
      <textCn>是的，谁说不是呢！</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I read she's twenty-nine, but she must be at least forty.</text>
      <textCn>我从报上看到她是29岁，但她一定至少有40岁了。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I'm sure she is.</text>
      <textCn>我肯定她有40岁了。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>She was a famous actress when I was still at school.</text>
      <textCn>当我还是学生时，她就是个著名的演员了。</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>That was a long time ago, wasn't it?</text>
      <textCn>那是好久以前的事了，是吗？</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>Not that long ago!</text>
      <textCn>不，没有那么久！</textCn>
    </sentence>
    <sentence>
      <text>I'm not more than twenty-nine myself.</text>
      <textCn>我自己现在还没过29岁呢。</textCn>
    </sentence>
  </sentences>
</lesson>